You enter a word when the program asks for it.

The program opens the dictionary file (a normal text file).

It reads the file one line at a time.

Each line in the file has a word followed by a colon and its meaning.
Example:
linux: an open-source operating system kernel

The program checks if the line starts with the same word you typed.

If it matches, it takes the meaning written after the colon and shows it to you.

